BEGIN_TEXT

Consider a linear transformation \( T(x)=Ax \) from \( {\mathbb R}^2 \) to \( {\mathbb R}^2 \).
Suppose for two vectors \(v_1\) and \(v_2\) in \( {\mathbb R}^2 \) we have \(T(v_1)=$a v_2\) and \(T(v_2)=$b v_1\).
Find the determinant of the matrix \(A\). 
$BR
\( \det \, (A) =\) \{ans_rule(10)\} 

END_TEXT

